Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.
Boil the @Spaghetti{180%g}, ~{8%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan.
Drizzle with oil and stir through.

Stir the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Peri Peri Seasoning{1%sachet}, @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Honey{1/2%tbsp} and @Water{150%ml} into the chicken.
Bring to the boil, then simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} and @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the pasta into the sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Share the pasta between your bowls.
Enjoy!